item.title: CVE-2022-4383|2024-08-03T01:41:44.402Z -- unknown -- cbx%20petition%20for%20wordpress
item.description: The CBX Petition for WordPress plugin through 1.0.3 does not properly sanitize and escape a parameter before using it in a SQL statement via an AJAX action available to unauthenticated users, leading to a SQL injection.
